open command promant/terminal



1]Install Python
  If Python is not installed:
``Download it from: https://www.python.org/downloads/
``During installation, make sure to check the box that says "Add Python to PATH"

2]  Clone the GitHub Repository:
    Open Command Prompt or Terminal, and run: ##don't include '{}' they indicate the code lines
    {
     git clone https://github.com/Cyberstan-UAV/simple-hand-gesture-recognization.git
     cd simple-hand-gesture-recognization
     }
3]   Set Up Virtual Environment (Recommended):
    
# For Windows
    {
     python -m venv venv
     venv\Scripts\activate    
    }
    
# For macOS/Linux:
    {
     source venv/bin/activate
    }

4]  Install Required Python Libraries
{
pip install -r requirements.txt
}

5]   folder:
     make sure your: Main.py
                     hand_tracking.py
                  &  requirements.txt
      are in same folder 

7. Python File Descriptions
main.py – This is your main script that:
           Captures webcam input
           Detects hand gestures using MediaPipe
           Maps specific gestures to mouse or volume actions using PyAutoGUI

hand_tracking.py – Custom wrapper class for:
                   initializing MediaPipe Hand module
                   Drawing landmarks
                   Extracting finger positions


8]    Run the Project
      In the project root directory (folder where you have everything), run:
    {
    python main.py
    }

